Defendant Calvin J Williams in court with attorney Jorge R Fragoso.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Amended Complaint filed. Reading waived.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Counts 1 and 2.  Court finds defendant guilty.

Court orders the following: 
Ct. 1:
- 5 months jail straight time - consecutive - STAYED for 2 years Probation - concurrent to Ct. 2
- Fine of $399.00 (includes DRGOD) to be paid as a Condition of Probation 
- Conditions of  Probation:  Follow thru with any treatment/counseling recommended by Agent.   Maintain full-time employment and/or combination of schooling.  No contact with Taylor Landscaping or Michael Taylor. Criminal Thinking. 
- DNA surcharge is waived.
- Defendant to perform 100 hours of community service within 2 years as a condition of probation.
- 10 days jail Condition Time (nonworking hours) STAYED to be used at the Agents discretion. Huber/Straight time to be used at the Agents discretion. 

Ct.  2:
- 5 months jail straight time - consecutive - STAYED for 2 years Probation - concurrent to Ct. 1
- Fine of $389.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation 
- Conditions of  Probation:  Follow thru with any treatment/counseling recommended by Agent.   Maintain full-time employment and/or combination of schooling.  No contact with Taylor Landscaping or Michael Taylor. Criminal Thinking. 
- DNA surcharge is waived.
